fields.name: Water
fields.description: Make sure you are drinking at least six to eight glasses of water each day for a myriad of health benefits and a healthy alternative to soda.

fields.name: Walking and Running
fields.description: Walking or running for a total of 20-30 minutes each day helps keep your heart healthy and it's fine to do shorter sessions throughout the day.

fields.name: Vegetables
fields.description: If you're not already getting your five servings of vegetables per day start out adding a few servings of broccoli or other green vegetables each week.

fields.name: Salmon and Omega-3s
fields.description: One or two servings of salmon or other sources of omega-3 fats offers many health benefits.

fields.name: Fruit
fields.description: Make fruit a part of your five a day with your favorite fruits.

fields.name: Legumes
fields.description: Legumes such as peas and beans are excellent sources of protein and fiber. Add a few servings to your meals per week.

fields.name: Calcium
fields.description: Maintain strong bones for life with foods rich in calcium such as milk, cheese, and yogurt or non-dairy sources.

fields.name: Protein
fields.description: Include healthy vegetarian and non-vegetarian sources of protein in your diet each day to fuel your workouts and maintain muscle.
